# Type-cast policy (Effect-TS idioms)

Researched against the vendored Effect 3.21.2 source (src/.effect). Splits the project's type
casts into "replace with an Effect idiom" vs "acceptable boundary cast". Full scratch investigation
lived in research-effect-type-safety.md (gitignored working-tree scratch).

## Replace — unsafe or redundant casts
- `JSON.parse(content) as T` (src/services/soul-fs.ts, readJsonFile) — untyped parse. Decode via
  Schema instead: Schema.decodeUnknownSync / decodeUnknownEither (src/.effect/packages/effect/src/
  Schema.ts:472, 595). The project already has SoulManifestDataSchema + decodeOrThrow and
  ActiveSoulSchema, so validating the parsed value is machinery already present; the cast skipped it.
- `return { _tag: "…" } as SoulHeartbeatResult` ×4 (src/commands.ts) — an object literal widened,
  then asserted onto the union. Use `satisfies SoulHeartbeatResult` (validates the literal without
  the unsafe widening a cast performs). Heavier alternative if the result type grows: Data.taggedEnum
  (src/.effect/packages/effect/src/Data.ts:464) with $is/$match. Project had zero `satisfies` uses.
- `(cause as Error).message` (src/services/soul-fs.ts) — casting an unknown catch value. Guard:
  `cause instanceof Error ? cause.message : String(cause)`. Effect models caught defects as unknown
  (Cause.defects, src/.effect/packages/effect/src/Cause.ts) precisely because they are not Error.
- `[] as SoulManifest[]` (src/commands.ts) — annotate the return type instead of asserting the literal.

## Keep — acceptable boundary casts, not defects
- `Object.keys(x) as Array<keyof …>` — Effect ITSELF casts identically in Record.keys
  (src/.effect/packages/effect/src/Record.ts:958) and Struct.keys (Struct.ts:222). A TypeScript
  limitation; no safer idiom exists. "Fixing" it would be cargo-cult ceremony.
- `as unknown as ExtensionAPI` / `as unknown as AppRuntime` (tests) — boundary casts building test
  doubles for an EXTERNAL SDK interface (Pi). Effect uses Layer.succeed(Tag, impl) only for its own
  Service tags; there is no Effect idiom for a third-party interface. Flagged honestly in the test.
- `as const` (×41) — literal narrowing, not unsafe assertions. Not a target.

## Verdict
The project is largely type-robust already; the one real gap was the untyped JSON.parse sitting next
to the schema that should validate it. Fix the four above; leave the three boundary casts alone.
